        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 3:14AM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 314 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hoopeston, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Danville, Hoopeston, Rossville, Vermilion Regional Airport, Bismarck,
Henning, and Alvin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
